Subject: Alumni, St. Patrick’s Day is Coming
Body:
<https://illinois.edu/emailer/files/157443/banner.jpg> 	
 	  

The University of Illinois Alumni Alliance
2018 Young Alumni Travel Program
Trips for 20-35 year olds

Hops, Grains & Slainte
An Irish Journey of Taste, Adventure & Knowledge

Appreciate insights into the art of distilling whiskey.

Be amazed by farm-to-table cuisine.

Or simply experience the best of what Ireland has to offer!

Travel in a small group from Dingle to Cork to Dublin and explore famous distilleries, sample craft beers, discover organic farms, see stunning castles and the most beautiful countryside, make new friends for life and network with like-minded people.

Book and pay in full by St. Patrick’s Day and SAVE
View this Discount <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13270162?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=1&finder=4145588333&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>

Subject: You're Invited: Genomic Science Shaping Tomorrow’s World
Body:
Click here to see this online <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13513928?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=1&finder=4145024404&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> 	
 	
 <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13513929?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=2&finder=4145024404&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> 	
 	
 	The College of LAS Alumni Association in partnership with the Carl R. Woese Institute for Genomic Biology presents

 <https://illinois.edu/emailer/files/159406/processed_822973.png?p=0208T160249> 	
 	
 	
Genomic Science Shaping Tomorrow’s World 

Innovations and Discoveries by LAS Professors 

 

Thursday, April 5, 2018

5:30-7:30 p.m.

Carl R. Woese Institute for Genomic Biology

1206 W. Gregory Drive, Urbana

 	
 	
 	
Genomic science at Illinois today is shaping our future tomorrow.  Please join us to learn what your future holds. 

You are invited to join fellow alumni, faculty, and friends for a fascinating evening discovering the world of genomic science at Illinois.  Learn first-hand about innovative and groundbreaking research from award-winning scientists Brendan Harley, Paul Hergenrother, and Donald Ort. 

The Harry E. Preble Dean of the College of LAS, Feng Sheng Hu, invites you to meet the director of the Carl R. Woese Institute for Genomic Biology, Gene Robinson, to learn about the dynamic research of these faculty who work in multi-disciplinary teams.  You will enjoy a reception, inspiring presentations by LAS scientists, a tour of this state-of-the-art facility, and stimulating conversation over coffee and dessert.

The Carl R. Woese Institute for Genomic Biology <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13513930?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=3&finder=4145024404&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  is an interdisciplinary institute dedicated to transformative research and technology in life sciences using team-based strategies to tackle grand societal challenges. Advances in genomics are fundamental to improving medicine, agriculture, nanotechnology, and manufacturing.

 	
 	
 	
REGISTER TODAY! <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13513931?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=4&finder=4145024404&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  Registration ends March 30, 2018    

Registration Fee: $25 per person 

For additional information, please call the Alumni Relations Office at (217) 333-3387 or email us <mailto:las-alum@illinois.edu> .

This event is partially funded by a generous gift from alumna and former board member, Alice Faron, and her husband, Jim Faron.

Subject: NovaCentauri42, the first Destiny Update for 2018 is here!
Body:
Earn Masterwork Armor and fight in the Iron Banner 
 <http://image.info.bungie.net/lib/fe911370756002787d/m/2/C121_Header.jpg> 	
 <http://click.info.bungie.net/?qs=87215fa5c832839e1992fb8393eb8daee92feedc05f6b1d5d8cd4305fbf317041f4668c411c97d78ddacdcaa44af6d8c62aff1c7e3a2d0e0> 	 
MASTER YOUR ARMOR 	
Have you acquired a Masterwork Weapon yet? Now you can earn armor with upgrade paths that lead to a different stat package. Each Masterwork Armor piece that you equip will help you resist enemy attacks when you use your super ability. 
 <http://click.info.bungie.net/?qs=87215fa5c832839efe53808ff42d04dbd4c7169ea2489b4146c5ea0195f80f41a0945bdf279c8816bed5ce2ed4b8db78a1a5b1eee9b25d52> 	 
That's not all you'll find in our January Update. If you love Raids, your existing gear can receive special Raid perks. The Raid vendor in the Tower will even sell Raid specific armor and weapons. If you have Raid tokens and Legendary Shards visit the Raid vendor in the Bazaar. 
 <http://click.info.bungie.net/?qs=87215fa5c832839e1992fb8393eb8daee92feedc05f6b1d5d8cd4305fbf317041f4668c411c97d78ddacdcaa44af6d8c62aff1c7e3a2d0e0> 	 
All of these updates are available to every player of Destiny 2. 
SEE WHAT'S IN THE JANUARY UPDATE <http://click.info.bungie.net/?qs=87215fa5c832839e22cb88ada8a9ee8ad8a535416fed45baff51c4b168ca6085862f2d0de3116920303ef8de89c42ef4cc8b12282aa638b2>

Subject: Noteworthy at Illinois
Body:
Click here to see this online <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13301779?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=1&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> 	
 	
 <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13301780?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=2&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> 	
 	
 	A new monthly e-newsletter where Chancellor Robert Jones shares campus news, stories, successes and information

Welcome Back to Campus
 <https://illinois.edu/emailer/files/157622/processed_806462.png?p=0129T024829> 	 	
 	

I hope everyone is having a good start to 2018. Whether you're a student starting a new semester of classes here at Illinois or one of our alumni living across the globe, I hope you accomplish the goals you've made for this year. If you'd like to see a snapshot of what I'm doing this semester, please consider following my Instagram account @IlliniChancellor <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306141?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=3&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  to stay in touch. I look forward to what new work, experiences and memories the new year will bring. 

Sincerely,

Robert J. Jones
Chancellor

 	
Find Illinois In the News
(The New York Times <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306142?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=4&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> ) Illinois law professor Robin Fretwell discusses how social issues might influence looming statehouse elections. 
(Ag Web <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306143?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=5&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> ) Researchers at Illinois have found that the more soy-based foods a person eats, the less likely they are to get prostate cancer. 
(Sports Illustrated <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306144?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=6&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> ) Illinois alumna and bobsledder Aja Evans is pushing toward a second Olympics appearance. 
(The Chronicle of Higher Education <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306145?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=7&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> ) The University of Illinois Board of Trustees has voted to freeze tuition for in-state freshmen for the fourth straight year, matching the longest consecutive freeze in more than four decades. 

 	
Learn About Illinois Legends
 <https://illinois.edu/emailer/files/157622/processed_806465.png?p=0129T024829> 	 	
 	

“Illinois Icons <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306146?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoocom&orderId=8&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> ” is a new 30-minute documentary that celebrates the legacy of three men who left enduring marks. Architect Max Abramovitz designed the Krannert Center for the Peforming Arts and what is now State Farm Center, along with the United Nations complex. Robert Zuppke is the most successful football coach in Illinois history. His coaching career includes four national college titles and induction into the national College Football Hall of Fame. Artist Lorado Taft created the iconic Alma Mater statue for Illinois in 1929. It has endured as the most iconic landmark on campus.

 	
Celebrate an Innovation Milestone
January 24th marked the 25th birthday of Mosaic, the first popular web browser. The technology was quickly transferred to the private sector and helped to shape the future of the online world. Interested in learning more? Read this article <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306147?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoocom&orderId=9&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  from NCSA. 

 	
Discover World-Changing Research
 <https://illinois.edu/emailer/files/157622/processed_806474.png?p=0129T024829> 	 	
 	

Empowering People <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306149?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=10&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  – A new study by Illinois educational psychology professor Christopher Napolitano says the key to willpower is believing you have it in abundance.
Improving Education <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306150?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=11&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  - Natural resources and environmental sciences professor Ming Kuo has found that student engagement in the classroom improved after an outdoor lesson.
Advancing Technology <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306151?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=12&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  - Illinois student Benjamin Sohn has used sound waves to produce optical diodes that fit onto a computer chip.
Shaping Health <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306152?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=13&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7>  - According to speech and hearing science professor Brian Monson, preterm babies may suffer auditory setbacks in the brain.  

 	
Attend a Sesquicentennial Concert
To mark a historical milestone in our university’s history, a special Sesquicentennial concert tour is coming to Chicago, New York and Champaign-Urbana this spring. The concerts, titled Gathering, will be performed by the University of Illinois Wind Symphony and Chamber Singers, and will be joined by soloists Nathan Gunn, Todd Payne and Yvonne Redman. Tickets are on sale now <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306153?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=14&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> . 

 	
Celebrate our Rankings, Awards & Honors
 <https://illinois.edu/emailer/files/157622/processed_806480.png?p=0129T024829> 	 	
 	

The Gies College of Business has been named one of the 10 business schools to watch in 2018 by Poets & Quants <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306154?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=15&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> .
Professors Donna Buchanan, Elizabeth Hoiem, Candice Jenkins, Paul Kapp, D. Fairchild Ruggles and Craig Williams have been awarded National Endowment for the Humanities Fellowships <https://illinoisedu/emailer/forward2/13306156?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=16&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> . Professors Antoinette Burton and Nathan Gunn have been named Swanlund Endowed Chairs <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306157?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=17&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> . Professors Stephen P. Long and Jeffrey S. Moore have been named Stanley O. Ikenberry Endowed Chairs <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306157?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=18&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> . 
Illinois alumna Poala Boivin has been named to the College Football Playoff selection committee <https://illinois.edu/emailer/forward2/13306158?emailAddress=aznmadness42@yahoo.com&orderId=19&finder=4127661629&constituentId=d3249b53-6635-42a5-a6e9-c0f38334f5c7> .

Subject: 2 Weeks Left! Apply to VSCO Voices
Body:
<https://vscovoices.co/application>  	
 	 
 	 
A VSCO + Access Ventures Creator Grant 

 	 
 	 
 	 
You have two weeks left to apply to VSCO Voices — the six month grant program that provides mentorship and $20,000 in funding for creators dedicated to empowering marginalized communities in the United States.

Designed to highlight the things that make us human and bring people together through art, this year’s project theme is Home. 

 	 
 	  	  	 
 	 Apply Now <https://vscovoices.co/application>  	 	 
 	  	  	 
 	 

 	 
We will close the application on Sunday, March 4th at 11:59pm PT. To qualify for the grant, you must be a VSCO community member, US-based, and at least 18 years of age. 

We’re excited to build the VSCO Voices community together.

The team at VSCO

Subject: Get out There! Affordable Last Minute Plans in Seattle This Weekend: 12 Minutes Max, Tavi Gevinson, Acapulco Lips, and More $10-and-under Events!
Body:

Subject: NWAA Presents Anne Lamott and Lindy West
Body:
Two powerful women of literature and humor at Benaroya Hall.

View in Email Browser <http://archive.skem1.com/csb/Public/show/mwkx8--etu5a-5j0p9vu5> 

 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/BH_photos/BH%20_%20A%20GLANCE/1718/1718%20eBlast_BH_Headers_Spotlight.jpg> 

	
	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/BH_photos/BH%20_%20A%20GLANCE/1718/1718_0408_Lamott_570.jpg> 

"Hope begins in the dark, the stubborn hope that if you just show up and try to do the right thing, the dawn will come." – Anne Lamott


SUNDAY, APRIL 8, AT 7:30PM

AN EVENING WITH ANNE LAMOTT


Presented by NWAA, KNKX 88.5FM & The Stranger

Seattle audiences have the opportunity to spend an evening with Anne Lamott, who writes and speaks about subjects that begin with capital letters: Alcoholism, Motherhood, Jesus. But armed with self-effacing humor — she is laugh-out-loud funny — and ruthless honesty, Lamott converts her subjects into enchantment. She doesn’t try to sugar-coat the sadness, frustration and disappointment, but tells her stories with honesty, compassion and a pureness of voice. Lamott does communicate her faith; she lifts, comforts, and inspires, all the while keeping us laughing.

 <http://click.skem1.com/click/mwkx8-dlpp7g-5j0p9vu6/> 

	
	
	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/BH_photos/BH%20_%20A%20GLANCE/1718/1718_0408_West_570.jpg> 

"We only get one life. Wasting someone’s time is the subtlest form of murder." – Lindy West


SUNDAY, APRIL 15, AT 7:30PM

LINDY WEST:
THE WITCHES ARE COMING


Presented by NWAA, KNKX 88.5FM & The Stranger

In this multi-media talk, bestselling author, contributor to This American Life, and New York Times opinion writer Lindy West discusses the power of personal storytelling and humor in the war for truth. Hailed by Lena Dunham as an "essential (and hilarious) voice for women," Lindy West is ferociously witty and outspoken, tackling topics as varied as pop culture, social justice and body image.

 <http://click.skem1.com/click/mwkx8-dlpp7i-5j0p9vu8/> 

	
	
	
BENAROYA HALL

Subject: Unity Tutorial- 2D Physics Overview
Body:
Learn to create convincing physical behavior.	 
View this email in your browser <http://app.response.unity3d.com/e/es?s=795651218&e=13682349&elqTrackId=1124a5578ef040b9a36354a958bae872&elq=35147e167d5144c6874a0c62ac5c91f7&elqaid=3591&elqat=1> 	 
	 <http://app.response.unity3d.com/e/er?utm_campaign=engine_global_nurture_Nurture%20beginners%20PE&utm_content=19-nurture-beginner-tutorial&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Eloqua&s=795651218&lid=404&elqTrackId=e3b431f4e58940bda180bc9a00eed1b3&elq=35147e167d5144c6874a0c62ac5c91f7&elqaid=3591&elqat=1> 	 	
 <http://images.response.unity3d.com/EloquaImages/clients/Unity/%7B2430a25b-f05b-4189-8bce-9fa819e8a45e%7D_tutorialtop.jpg> 
	Tutorial
		
	Hi Casey, 		
	I’m sure you’ve seen when a game object does not properly accelerate, or a collision looks clumsy, or gravity does not perform realistically. Poorly balanced physics are distracting, and ultimately detrimental to gameplay.

In this 10 part video tutorial, you will learn the basics of 2D physics. 2D Rigidbody, Collider, Hinge Joint, Spring Joint and character controllers are all covered in detail. Watch your once static sprites come to life with realistic 2D movements. Get familiar with the 2D physics components in Unity and ensure your mechanics are fun and responsive.

Get up to speed on 2D physics today, check out the 2D Physics Overview. <http://app.response.unity3d.com/e/er?utm_campaign=engine_global_nurture_Nurture%20beginners%20PE&utm_content=19-nurture-beginner-tutorial&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Eloqua&s=795651218&lid=2849&elqTrackId=ee709ab7bc37451b95ab505620008150&elq=35147e167d5144c6874a0c62ac5c91f7&elqaid=3591&elqat=1> 

Yours in development,	 	
 <http://images.response.unity3d.com/EloquaImages/clients/Unity/%7B3d7ba327-a8e4-4730-a446-6e02b9f81706%7D_Screen_Shot_2017-02-06_at_5.35.07_PM.png> 	 <http://images.response.unity3d.com/EloquaImages/clients/Unity/%7Be7f6159a-5cc6-4177-8373-699842d5d4b5%7D_Signatures_Adam_1.png> 
Adam Buckner
Online Evangelism

 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	How to Redeem your Reward 

You collected 125 Stars, which means you've earned a free drink or food item. Here's what to do:	  <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	1. Choose almost anything on the menu	 
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	2. Tell your barista you'd like to redeem a 
    Reward	 
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	3. Scan with your Starbucks® app or your
    registered Starbucks Card	 
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	You can also redeem your reward when you order ahead in the Starbucks app. Simply click 'Redeem' on the Confirm Order screen to use your reward.	  <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	
 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif> 	
 <http://e.starbucks.com/a/hBahVIDAJvkyvB9PZQTNtmpcAH7/logo>

 <http://f.e.starbucks.com/i/52/163466415/080213-sbux-summer2-week8-d1-space.gif>

Subject: Two Events Back To Back
Body:
Be My Valentine
Maximus Jingles - Gladiator Video
Lunar New Year - Year of the Dog 	
View this email in your browser <http://mailchi.mp/edgecasegames/feb12022018?e=4196722705> 

T <https://fracturedspace.us3.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=f7878b3a361075d05241d1728&id=a0c035dc17&e=4196722705&c=32bb233cef> oo many emails? Unsubscribe <https://fracturedspace.us3.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=f7878b3a361075d05241d1728&id=a0c035dc17&e=4196722705&c=32bb233cef>  	
 <https://gallery.mailchimp.com/f7878b3a361075d05241d1728/images/079b013e-96c4-49e1-b16f-d0f414a3d4fd.png> 	

There's still time to capture their hearts and mines


Greetings Lovestruck Captains,

It seems some of the Crew got a little hasty and thought yesterday was the only day to show their true love, little do they realize that love is eternal and not just for a day. There is still time to finish off the 30 Mine Captures necessary to have Jules Valentine added to your Crew Barracks before 1800 UTC Thurs Feb 15th

The Crimson Skins Bundle is also still 50% off until Thurs 15th Feb 1800 UTC, if you fancy wearing the color of "lurve" all year round.

See in-game for more details.

 

 <https://fracturedspace.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=f7878b3a361075d05241d1728&id=3ad743ee9f&e=4196722705> 	
ARE YOU NOT ENTERTAINED?! Jingles takes one of the NEW Gladiator Ultimate Skins for a test drive. 	
	
 <https://gallery.mailchimp.com/f7878b3a361075d05241d1728/images/2b8771a4-8b66-4fba-a927-66f2fa4f1826.png> 	

Lunar New Year - Year of the Dog

Earn yourselves the Five Star Red skins for the TDS Leviathan and the TDS Protector by working as a team and securing 120,000 Takedowns together by the end of play on Monday 19th Feb 2018 1800 UTC.

During this time we will also be bringing back the rest of the Five Star Red collection to the store and Captains that take part during this time will earn themselves a unique Event Badge to show their dedication to the new year.

See in-game for more details.  
	
WOULD YOU LIKE TO RECEIVE FRACTURED SPACE SPECIAL OFFERS ON PLATINUM, SHIPS, SKINS AND MORE? <https://fracturedspace.us3.list-manage.com/profile?u=f7878b3a361075d05241d1728&id=a0c035dc17&e=4196722705>

Subject: The Goulet Communiqué: February 14, 2018
Body:
Pilot Hand Lettering Boxed Sets, the Monteverde Invincia Nebula, and more...     View this email in your browser <http://mailchi.mp/gouletpens/the-goulet-communique-february-1417497?e=58056be300> 
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=3b9f112aec&e=58056be300> 	
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=c1f613304d&e=58056be300> 	
New Visconti Rembrandt <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=b9c7155345&e=58056be300>  colors have arrived! We now have Twilight, Eclipse, Dark Forest, and Pink! These beautiful pens emulate Rembrandt’s painting technique with small marblings of light in the resin. To learn more, check out our blog <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=9d0b3a5d60&e=58056be300> .
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=b5091a8583&e=58056be300> 	
If you haven’t heard yet, LAMY VibrantPink <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=d1adcc108e&e=58056be300>  is here! Don't let this special edition AL-Star and ink pass you by! 
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=bb85d58837&e=58056be300> 	
The Monteverde Regatta Sport <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=ad2a40d1a4&e=58056be300>  is one of the most adventurous pens around! It features alternating bands of black carbon fiber and a magnetic closure for both closing and posting.
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=2675686c91&e=58056be300> 	
The new Aurora 88 Minerali Amber <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=2e0d790063&e=58056be300>  is a stunning new demonstrator that you’re going to want in your pen case. This pen has a rhodium-plated 18k gold nib and features Aurora’s Hidden Reservoir filling system. 
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=0a4e4e9875&e=58056be300> 	
Hand lettering doesn’t have to be as hard as it looks! We now offer Pilot Hand Lettering Boxed Sets <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=c4f909f6cb&e=58056be300> , which include multiple pens, ink cartridges, and a hand lettering guidebook. These are a perfect gift for your favorite aspiring artist!
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=233c3f498b&e=58056be300> 	
The striking Stipula Etruria Tortoise <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=6e4cf811c5&e=58056be300>  is the commanding pen you've been looking for. This pen's body is made from Italian hand-turned resin and features matte gold accents. If you prefer a stealthier pen check out the black Stipula Etruria Gorilla <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=064c6b1af5&e=58056be300> . 
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=cb1d43a7d4&e=58056be300> 	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=ca49239942&e=58056be300> 	
The Conklin Duraflex <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=a8e3787569&e=58056be300>  is coming soon to help you add a little flair to your writing! This new pen features the OmniFlex nib, which was designed and cut for maximum performance.
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=6a6169ccf0&e=58056be300> 	
The new Monteverde Invincia Nebula <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=1c8e9311b6&e=58056be300>  is out of this world! This pen features a multi-colored plating finish of blues, purples, and reds. Arriving in the next few weeks. 
	
	
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=91041925f0&e=58056be300> 	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=df11acea14&e=58056be300> 	
Last week marked the 200th episode <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=dd344dc9f0&e=58056be300>  of Goulet Q&A! In this very special episode, you get a behind-the-scenes look at our new office.
	
 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=66a8718695&e=58056be300> 	
Monteverde California Teal is a gorgeous ink that we thought deserved a closer look! Check out our new ink review <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=d916105a30&e=58056be300>  by Kelsi to see it in action. 
	
 <https://gallery.mailchimp.com/285169d5958e74e317878186c/images/d5d81045-852f-4030-b411-f5fe1766fcab.jpg> 	
Hi pen friends, 
 
We started something new within the last week called Write Now, a video series where we have several members of our team speak casually about the products we're using and testing every day. We shoot in the morning, and publish a few hours later. It's been an absolute blast for us to shoot these, and we've done 4 already since Thursday last week! We were originally planning on 2 a week but we may end up with more. Be sure to head on over to YouTube and subscribe so you can be in the loop on these. Part of the reason we want to do it is to show more than just Brian, because others on our team know and love pens, too! And to get to show more pens in use, in a more conversational style than the reviews we've done for years. Because it's so fun and efficient for us to produce, we're able to share so much more with you than the highly produced formal pen reviews. Check them out <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=b4346ec045&e=58056be300>  and let us know what you think!

We also had a chance to share a tour of our new office in Q&A 200 <https://gouletpens.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=285169d5958e74e317878186c&id=2a601a689d&e=58056be300> , and we've gotten quite a reaction so far! It was a huge deal for us to share this with you all, and we're overwhelmed with the gratitude you've all expressed to us. We have plans for even more and better things to serve you in 2018, here's to what's to come! 

Write on,
 <https://gallery.mailchimp.com/285169d5958e74e317878186c/images/af4f44a6-ac69-4b39-875d-89b1ae08d63e.jpg>

Subject: Lisa Fischer, Fran Lebowitz and Jake Shimabukuro!
Body:
Plus! Live @ Benaroya Hall in February
View email as webpage <http://archive.skem1.com/csb/Public/show/mu3jq--esxk3-5j0p9vu0> 

 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_Headers/1718 eBlast_MarketingSeason_thisweeknextweek.jpg> 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_TWNW/POPS4_570.jpg> 	
FRIDAY, FEBRUARY 16, AT 8PM
SATURDAY, FEBRUARY 17, AT 8PM
SUNDAY, FEBRUARY 18, AT 2PM


JUST A KISS AWAY! 
WITH LISA FISCHER, GRAND BATON 
& THE SEATTLE SYMPHONY 


SEATTLE POPS Title Sponsor: MCM



The unforgettable Lisa Fischer spent decades singing her heart out with The Rolling Stones, Tina Turner, Luther Vandross and Chris Botti. Twenty Feet from Stardom, the Oscar-winning documentary, brought Lisa center stage. Now, the two-time Grammy winner is touring the world, recording with Yo-Yo Ma and Lang Lang and thrilling critics and fans. In this new program, Lisa recreates rock anthems like "Gimme Shelter" and "Rock and Roll" using the rich colors and textures of the orchestra.



 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_Buttons/1617 eBlast buttons_chooseyourseats.jpg> 

			
 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_LBH/1718-0218-FranLebowitz-570.jpg> 	
SUNDAY, FEBRUARY 18, AT 7:30PM


FRAN LEBOWITZ:  AUTHOR, JOURNALIST & SOCIAL OBSERVER


Live @ Benaroya Hall


 

In a cultural landscape filled with endless pundits and talking heads, Fran Lebowitz stands out as one of our most insightful social commentators. Her writing offers insights on timely issues such as gender, race, gay rights and the media, as well as her own pet peeves — among them celebrity culture, tourists and strollers. The New York Times Book Review calls Lebowitz an "important humorist in the classic tradition." Purveyor of urban cool, Leibowitz is a cultural satirist who has often been named a modern Dorothy Parker.



Now, Fran brings her acerbic views on current events (including Trump, tax bills and more) and the media to the Benaroya Hall stage for an exclusive one-night-only engagement. Lebowitz will be interviewed by Paul Constant, co-founder of The Seattle Review of Books.

 

 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_Buttons/1617 eBlast buttons_chooseyourseats.jpg> 

			
 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_LBH/JakeShimabukuro_570x250.jpg> 	
MONDAY, FEBRUARY 19, AT 7:30PM


JAKE SHIMABUKURO


Live @ Benaroya Hall


 

Jake Shimabukuro has elevated the ukulele from a beloved Hawaiian folk instrument to a world-class vehicle, fearlessly traversing boundaries and putting his inspired touch on everything from Queen’s “Bohemian Rhapsody” to Schubert's “Ave Maria.” And he can still vividly remember the first time he held a ukulele, at age four. “I fell in love with the ukulele immediately,” Jake recalls. “From that day on, you had to pry the instrument away from me in order to get me to do anything else.”



In Jake’s early touring days, everyone was surprised that he could even attempt such complex music on such a humble instrument. But now, they know better. Jake has drawn comparisons to musical titans such as Jimi Hendrix and Miles Davis, has collaborated with everyone from Yo-Yo Ma to Cyndi Lauper, and was the subject of an acclaimed 2012 documentary, Jake Shimabukuro: Life on Four Strings. 

 

 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_Buttons/1617 eBlast buttons_chooseyourseats.jpg> 

			
 	
 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_TWNW/1718-0216-MasonJennings-182.jpg> 	
FEBRUARY 16 
MASON JENNINGS



Lizzie Weber, opener

 

Minneapolis singer-songwriter Mason Jennings brings his soulful and sincere indie folk to the Benaroya Hall stage. He has toured the world for close to 20 years, cultivating a rootsy sound filled with introspective songwriting. His gentle tenor has drawn comparisons to Jack Johnson and Ray LaMontagne.


LEARN MORE

			
 	
 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_Trgts/BAR2-223_NW Boy Choir_182.jpg> 	
FEBRUARY 23 & 24
VIVALDI GLORIA


Dmitry Sinkovsky, conductor, countertenor & violin
Liv Redpath, soprano
Maria Männistö, soprano
Northwest Boychoir


J.C. BACH: Sinfonia in G minor
VIVALDI: Violin Concerto in D major, “per la solennità di San Lorenzo”
VIVALDI: Gloria

 

LEARN MORE

			
 	
 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_LBH/20170614_CARLA BRUNI_182.jpg> 	
FEBRUARY 25
CARLA BRUNI

 

Singer-songwriter Carla Bruni exudes an effortless elegance through her smoky, intimate alto vocals. This magnetic quality weaves through her latest English language album, French Touch (October 2017), where Bruni puts her indelible mark on covers of everything from Depeche Mode to AC/DC.



LEARN MORE

			
 	
 	
 	
 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_TWNW/1617 eBlast HOWTOORDER_172x172.jpg> 	
BUY TICKETS 


WEBSITE:
seattlesymphony.org

PHONE: 206.215.4747 <tel:2062154747?source_no=48408>  or
1.866.833.4747 (toll-free)

IN PERSON: Visit us at
Benaroya Hall, on the corner
of Third Avenue & Union
Street; Mon–Fri, 10am–6pm;
Sat, 1–6pm; 2 hours prior to
performances through
intermission.

LEARN MORE

			
 	
 	
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_Trgts/1617_Concerts_Strauss_Dvorak0929_Brandon-Patoc.jpg> 	
SYMPHONY ON AIR



Every Wednesday at 8pm, join KING FM host Dave Beck and a co-host from the Seattle Symphony to get an inside look at upcoming concerts before you hear them in the concert hall or over the airwaves.

Missed one of the Seattle Symphony Spotlights? Listen to Dave Beck’s most recent interviews on-demand! Click here to access the full Seattle Symphony podcast library.

LEARN MORE

			
 	
 	 
 	
 <http://media.mail2app.lynch2.com/media/50/501470/M_TWNW/gallery-muse-2172x172.jpg> 	
DINE AT BENAROYA


Enjoy pre-concert dining at Muse, just a few short steps from your seat. Muse blends the elegance of downtown dining with the casual comfort of nearby Pike Place Market. Open to ALL ticket holders two hours prior to select performances.

To make a reservation, please visit OpenTable or call 206.336.6699 <tel:2063366699?source_no=48408> .

Subject: Europe's Tastiest Tipples!
Body:
Email not displaying correctly? View it in your browser <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=babf3a16e9&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=457625e0fd&e=e4e3c753d9>   <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=c028cfee79&e=e4e3c753d9>   <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=6d401f642f&e=e4e3c753d9> 	Unsubscribe <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=398350a34a&e=e4e3c753d9&c=873b5e31cc> 	
 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=0be979dd47&e=e4e3c753d9> 	

Europe's Tastiest Tipples!

 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=f6659e9d7d&e=e4e3c753d9> 	Dear Casey, 

Inspired by our Annie's trip to Norway to taste some terrific tipples (read about it on the blog! <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=fe9a76ac67&e=e4e3c753d9> ), we've compiled a collection of fascinating spirits from across Europe!

First, we're stopping off in The Netherlands for a drop of Millstone single malt whisky, produced by Zuidam in Baarle-Nassau.

Our Single Cask Series bottling of Millstone 6 Year Old was matured in a single bourbon barrel and bottled at cask strength. It's got a flavour profile we would describe as "...a ball-pit of Chocolate Oranges". So, yeah. It's amazing.

£79.95	 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=fc1ad2ba78&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <http://cdn3.masterofmalt.com/resources/newsletter/header/v_2columns_separator.gif> 	

Napue Gin

 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=25c2f60e1c&e=e4e3c753d9> 	

The Kyrö Distillery Company in Isokyrö, Finland, makes the excellent Napue Gin using rye grain for its base spirit.

£34.95	 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=b01773e7d2&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <http://cdn2.masterofmalt.com/resources/newsletter/header/v_2columns_separator.gif> 	

O.P. Anderson

 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=606c35ba05&e=e4e3c753d9> 	

O.P. Anderson (produced in Gothenburg) is one of the oldest Swedish Aquavit brands, and it's still around today!

£29.95	 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=7e71033756&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <http://cdn3.masterofmalt.com/resources/newsletter/header/v_2columns_separator.gif> 	

Filliers' 38°

 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=4fe21f1d0d&e=e4e3c753d9> 	

Tucked away in Bachte-Maria-Leerne, Belgium, the Filliers distillery makes some of the best jenever you can find.

£32.95	 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=cb044c64f3&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <http://cdn2.masterofmalt.com/resources/newsletter/header/v_2columns_separator.gif> 	

Marka Nordic Bitter

 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=a9df39568d&e=e4e3c753d9> 	

Behold the aforementioned Norwegian deliciousness – Marka Nordic Bitter from Oslo Håndverksdestilleri!

£28.95	 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=1439a86b34&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=df684e6a85&e=e4e3c753d9> 	 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=4749091895&e=e4e3c753d9> 	

Belvedere Lake Bartezek


Säntis Malt

£43.83  <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=2df522a108&e=e4e3c753d9> 	£47.02  <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=d3b7874ef4&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=370dfe9d54&e=e4e3c753d9> 	 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=9f3ebd8e83&e=e4e3c753d9> 	

Tosolini Grappa di Chardonnay


Wolfschmidt Kummel

£27.83  <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=c8d5c1ce90&e=e4e3c753d9> 	£17.48  <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=d132af16e0&e=e4e3c753d9> 	
 <http://cdn2.masterofmalt.com/resources/newsletter/header/v_2columns_separator.gif> 	

The news in brief

 <http://cdn3.masterofmalt.com/resources/newsletter/header/v_2columns_separator.gif> 	
 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=5b10ce8032&e=e4e3c753d9> 	<https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=b1cfe1c228&e=e4e3c753d9> 

Exploring Oslo Håndverksdestilleri (OHD) in Norway


With its idyllic fjord, lush forested hills, bountiful indigenous botanicals and laid-back stance on foraging, Oslo is a city that practically lends itself to distilling.

Read more » <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=d8d8802b44&e=e4e3c753d9> 
 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=51749ce45f&e=e4e3c753d9> 	<https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=c0acd3f6d6&e=e4e3c753d9> 

Think pink: Introducing Beefeater London Pink!


Beefeater has become the latest distillery to jump on the bandwagon with the launch of its new strawberry-flavoured variant, Beefeater London Pink. Spoiler alert: it's delicious.

Read more » <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=ae95e690c0&e=e4e3c753d9> 
 <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=579b58a61a&e=e4e3c753d9> 	<https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=5de832e8e8&e=e4e3c753d9> 

The Nightcap: 9 February


Naked Swedish people, heart-breaking agave stats, and a newly-formed drinks thinktank that could change the future of booze marketing: it’s The Nightcap.

Read more » <https://masterofmalt.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e8912b97f8b90c0f25880a8a7&id=ddbe0da718&e=e4e3c753d9>

Hi Casey,

On February 13, 2018 at 3:42 PM, we noticed an attempt to sign in to your Yahoo account aznmadness42 from Washington, United States.

If this was you, please create an app password as you've enabled Second Sign-In Verification.

Steps for creating an app password are:

1. Visit https://login.yahoo.com/account and sign in to your Yahoo account.

2. Look for "App passwords", and click "Generate password".

3. Use your app password to sign in again.

If this wasn't you and you believe someone may have tried to access your account, please change your password by visiting: https://login.yahoo.com/account/change-password and update your account recovery information.

Thanks, 

Yahoo

Subject: JUST ANNOUNCED: A Special Concert with Macklemore & Ryan Lewis, Russell Wilson, Ciara and the Seattle Symphony!
Body:
A one-night-only event supporting youth, equity and access to the arts.
? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? 
View email as webpage <http://archive.skem1.com/csb/Public/show/mpcbk--eopju-5j0p9vu2>

 <http://click.skem1.com/click/mpcbk-dj2r26-5j0p9vu4/> 

THURSDAY, MAY 10 | 8PM
BENAROYA HALL



Macklemore & Ryan Lewis, Russell Wilson and Ciara join the Seattle Symphony for an inspirational benefit concert in support of youth, equity and access to the arts. This one-night-only event features Seattle celebrities alongside the next generation of artists for an unforgettable evening of music.



Concert proceeds support the initiatives and programs of the Macklemore & Ryan Lewis Equity Fund, Russell and Ciara's Why Not You Foundation and the Seattle Symphony's Education Programs. The evening will also feature performances by youth representing programs that will directly benefit from the concert.



 <http://click.skem1.com/click/mpcbk-dj2r27-5j0p9vu5/>

Subject: How'd You Like Spruce?
Body:
Hi Casey,

My name is Brian, and I’m part of the Bespoke Post team. We’re always trying to find new ways to improve your experience with Bespoke Post, and would love to hear your thoughts on the Spruce box. 

If you’re interested in participating, just click below to fill out a short survey. It’ll be shorter than the weekend always feels. That’s pretty short.

Take The Survey <http://link.bespokepost.com/click/12155071.>  

We really appreciate your time, and thanks for being a subscriber. 

Cheers,
Brian

Subject: How to start your own game dev company and follow your dream
Body:

	Connect	 	
	Hi Casey, 		
	Vera Velichko is brutally honest. She knew she wanted to run her own business but didn’t know how to start. In this developer story, she discusses the original idea, the early team, fragile friendships, and how a gaming conference crystallized their concept into a real start-up named Owl Studios.

Read how Owl Studios was self-aware enough to see its problems as well as its potential in publishing its first game titled One Day in London. From engine selection, to marketing, porting problems and whether a visual novel was the right genre, Vera shares her honest appraisal of publishing her first game and building her dream studio.

Read Vera's story here. <http://app.response.unity3d.com/e/er?utm_campaign=engine_global_nurture_Nurture%20beginners%20PE&utm_content=18-nurture-beginner-connect&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Eloqua&s=795651218&lid=3782&elqTrackId=df3124e8969a484183db859201f1ce93&elq=4d22041e14534fba9a782653e5b5d07a&elqaid=3594&elqat=1>

Who needs a romantic date night when you have SPiN and Bumble teaming up to celebrate love pong?!

Buzz over to SPiN Seattle, 1511 6th Ave, Seattle, WA 98101, for a game of love pong tomorrow from 9pm-2am. Drinks on us!

Get custom tattoos from Tattly with your Bumble BFF, connect with Bumble Buzz for some sweatworking & instructional tips in our private room, and witnesssurprise performances throughout the evening. Come with your friends, leave with a new match.

Subject: News from NOMOS Glashütte: iF Award and notes of love
Body:
<http://news.glashuette.com/supermailer/link.php?link=01_02_04_23A_1> 	
________________________________


A prizewinner on the wrist

 	
	 	
Good job, Metro neomatik 39 silvercut! The new automatic watch from the At Work series has just won the iF Award for NOMOS Glashütte. This is now the seventh time we have received this prestigious prize, which has been highlighting outstanding design for over 60 years and enjoys global recognition. We’re not the only ones who think that this latest version of Metro is an outstanding timepiece: Its horizontally-brushed dial, ultra-thin case, and neomatik caliber DUW 3001 has won over the expert jury of the iF Design Award as well. As you may already know, this model was created by Mark Braun, one of our favorite designers. 

more Metro <http://news.glashuette.com/supermailer/link.php?link=01_02_04_23A_A> 	
  
more awards <http://news.glashuette.com/supermailer/link.php?link=01_02_04_23A_C> 	
 	
________________________________


Watches with a love note (making every day Valentine’s Day)

 	
	 	
Soon—on February 14—it’ll be Valentine’s Day. Don’t give pralines or chocolates again, give a proper gift for a change: Tangente, Orion, Tetra, or another one of our watches. We now have many models with space for a love note; their stainless steel backs can feature four lines of 22 characters each.

So take a look and write your message, we’ll engrave and send it.

more to fall in love with <http://news.glashuette.com/supermailer/link.php?link=01_02_04_23A_B> 	
 	
________________________________


Basel secrets

 	
	 	
The highlight of the watchmaking calendar starts on March 22: Baselworld 2018. We can’t reveal much yet—but we can say that something exciting is racing our way! New watches, new innovations; a significant update for NOMOS Glashütte. Would you like to see more? Visit us in hall 1.1, stand E79. As well as on Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter.

like us on facebook! <http://news.glashuette.com/supermailer/link.php?link=01_02_04_23A_D>
